<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-225-131 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 853 125</DOCID><JOURNAL>The New York Times  Feb 7 1991 v140 pC17(N) pD20(L) 14 col in.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Nynex ties commercial to Gulf War. (Nynex Corp and the 1991Persian Gulf War)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Rothenberg, Randall.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Nynex Corp decides that it will use the Persian Gulf warbetween Iraq and the American-led coalition forces in itsadvertising.andP;  The telephone company says that its not a questionof whether or not to use the war in advertising, it is a questionof how to use it.andP;  Nynex's ad emphasizes that communication isimportant in times of stress.andP;  The company's ad is a 15-secondspot that includes black-and-white images of war spliced withimages from the home front.andP;  The ad ends with a color picture ofthe earth and states: 'never is information more crucial todemocracy than at times like these.'andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   NYNEX Corp. (Advertising).andO;Ticker:    NYN.andO;Topic:     Telephone companiesAdvertisingEthicsSocial Issues.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>